               <id root="af2cab60-fb46-4ad6-9e22-0b387040ceb9"/>
               <code code="34071-1" codeSystem="2.16.840.1.113883.6.1" displayName="WARNINGS SECTION"/>
               <title>Warning:</title>
               <text>
                  <paragraph styleCode="first">This Packet contains sodium fluoride powder, contents poisonous if swallowed. keep away from children. Store in a dry place at controlled room temperature. For professional use only.</paragraph>
                  <paragraph>DO NOT SWALLOW</paragraph>
                  <paragraph>MISSUSE If child swallows dispensed amount of mouth rinse in a cup:</paragraph>
                  <paragraph>1. Do not panic -this amount should not hurt the child</paragraph>
                  <paragraph>2. In rare cases the child may feel slightly nauseous.</paragraph>
                  <paragraph>The child may have a serving of milk or ice cream to relieve the nausea. EMERGENCY TREATMENT If a child swallows more than one dispensed amount in a cup or powder contents of the fluoride mouth rinse packet call the Poison Control Center at 800-222-1222</paragraph>
                  <paragraph/>
                  <paragraph/>
               </text>
               <effectiveTime value="20181214"/>
            </section>
         </component>
         <component>
            <section>
               <id root="2cce38b8-1561-4bfe-81b6-01477a46b5cc"/>
               <code code="34068-7" codeSystem="2.16.840.1.113883.6.1" displayName="DOSAGE &amp; ADMINISTRATION SECTION"/>
               <title>Directions</title>
               <text>
                  <paragraph>Mix contents with stated amount of tap water until dissolved (read directions on jug label) Makes an 0.2 % solution of sodium fluoride mouthrinse aftert dilution. Swish 10 ml (2 teaspoons) around vigorously in the mouth for one minute and then spit out. To be used once a week.</paragraph>
               </text>
               <effectiveTime value="20181214"/>
            </section>
